        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:42PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gallipolis, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Point Pleasant, Gallipolis, Buffalo, Crown City, Henderson, Leon,
Cheshire, Grimms Landing, Gallopolis Ferry, Lakin, Southside, and
Ashton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
